all community that aims to minimise its energy use in the highly industrialised city. Its name comes from the idea at the heart of the commune: no electricity, no plugs.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EWith South Korea among the highest carbon dioxide emitters globally, NoPlug hopes their community can make an impact by reducing their carbon footprint. Although it&rsquo;s not possible to be entirely emission free, the idea is to put electricity consumption at zero, and try to keep any energy generation from sustainable sources. Their living situation is a very different take on what it means to have a functional home; foregoing electricity, they rely on fuel sources such as solar and fire to do daily tasks (and even run a power-free coffee shop that&rsquo;s open from dawn until dusk).\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EDr Yasuyuki Fujimura, visits the NoPlug community from Japan each month to educate people on how to approach every day needs without electricity and appliances. &ldquo;I want to give a dream to young people who are now losing their hope,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s our duty.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"infographic","imageAlignment":"centre","pullQuoteImageAlignment":"centre","videoImageAlign":"centre","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20190905-living-without-electricity-in-the-heart-of-seoul-0"}],"collection":[],"disableAdverts":false,"displayDate":"2019-09-11T18:43:47Z","embeddedCustomHtml":"","embeddedInfographicUrl":"","embeddedType":"infographic","geolocation":null,"headlineLong":"Living without electricity in the heart of Seoul","headlineShort":"The coffee shop that’s off the grid","image":[],"imageAlignment":"centre","imageAltText":"","isSyndicated":true,"latitude":"","location":null,"longitude":"","mpsVideo":"","option":null,"partner":null,"primaryVertical":"worklife","promoAlignment":"centre","promoAltText":"","promoImage":null,"relatedStories":null,"relatedTag":null,"summaryLong":"A commune in the heart of 