ted.","businessUnit":"worldwide","cards":[{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EWith matters of money, millennials have an uphill climb.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat is the story we hear: millennials digging out from record student loan debt &ndash; expected to soar above \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Fnews\u002Feducation-44433569\"\u003E&pound;1tn ($1.27tn) in the UK\u003C\u002Fa\u003E over the next 25 years alone &ndash; and scrambling to pay rent with globally rising living costs and lower wages. And the numbers corroborate the story. Generation-on-generation wealth is declining, and \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.independent.co.uk\u002Fnews\u002Fbusiness\u002Fnews\u002Fyoung-people-will-be-poorer-than-their-parents-at-every-stage-of-life-ifs-finds-a6740511.html\"\u003Emillennials are financially worse off \u003C\u002Fa\u003Ethan those before them.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENone of this is exactly surprising, however. We have known for years that the 2008 global financial crisis hit millennials hard, with many graduating directly into a troubled global economy &ndash; from which \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Fcapital\u002Fstory\u002F20181107-what-it-takes-to-be-young-greek-and-able-to-pay-your-bills\"\u003Esome countries\u003C\u002Fa\u003E are still struggling to rebound entirely. Slow wage growth, high living costs and a lack of retirement savings mean millennials will be playing catch-up well into retirement.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-0"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"When baby boomers pass on their assets to younger family members, analysts expect them to leave $4tn of wealth to millennials within the UK and North America alone","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-1"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EThat&rsquo;s if they can afford to quit working at all. The World Economic Forum predicts that by 2050, when millennials in the world&rsquo;s eight largest pension markets start to retire, the \u003Ca href=\"http:\u002F\u002Fwww3.weforum.org\u002Fdocs\u002FWEF_White_Paper_We_Will_Live_to_100.pdf\"\u003Eretirement savings gap\u003C\u002Fa\u003E will be $427tn. That&rsquo;s more than six times the 2015 figure of $67tn. Driving this shortfall are things like longer life expectancy, the deceleration of a long-term growth environment and poor savings rates, coupled with low levels of financial literacy.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis doesn&rsquo;t paint a hopeful picture for the future &ndash; but maybe there is a scenario that is not so bleak. Could a windfall from the richest generation &ndash; baby boomers &ndash; reverse the fortunes for millennials?\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EShelter from the storm\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnlike millennials, baby boomers are the wealthiest generation in history &ndash; and will remain that way until \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww2.deloitte.com\u002Finsights\u002Fus\u002Fen\u002Findustry\u002Finvestment-management\u002Fus-generational-wealth-trends.html\"\u003Eroughly 2030\u003C\u002Fa\u003E.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAccording to a \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.rbcwealthmanagement.com\u002F_global\u002Fstatic\u002Fdocuments\u002FRBC-wealth-transfer-report-2017.pdf\"\u003Ewealth transfer report\u003C\u002Fa\u003E by the Royal Bank of Canada, when this group passes on their assets to younger family members, analysts expect them to leave $4tn of wealth to millennials within the UK and North America alone. This &lsquo;\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Fnews\u002Fuk-42519073\"\u003Einheritance boom&rsquo;\u003C\u002Fa\u003E will position millennials who have baby boomers in their families to receive record sums of inheritance.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-2"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":["p06tnsfx"],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-3"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EIs the solution to millennials&rsquo; money woes, then, to wait for the wealthier baby boomer generation to die out and inherit their assets?\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt&rsquo;s an argument made by Paul Donovan, UBS Wealth Management&rsquo;s chief global economist, who earlier this year predicted that millennials will actually become \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.businessinsider.de\u002Finterview-with-ubs-paul-donovan-on-millennials-and-inequality-2018-1\"\u003Ehistory&rsquo;s \u003Cem\u003Ewealthiest \u003C\u002Fem\u003Egeneration\u003C\u002Fa\u003E. Speaking to Business Insider, he argued that wealth doesn&rsquo;t evaporate from the economy. And, since baby boomers are a larger generation than millennials, wealth will consolidate as it is passed down through the generations. Simply: fewer people, the same amount of wealth distributed among them.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAll in the family\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt&rsquo;s not that simple, says Moritz Schularick, professor of economics at the University of Bonn in Germany. He says that the intergenerational wealth transfer model in which millennials become the wealthiest generation on record is a &ldquo;global top 1% model&rdquo;.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E&ldquo;It applies to people who have so much they can never spend their wealth,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;Normal people &ndash; and standard economic models &ndash; assume that people save for old age and then use their savings [and] wealth to pay for things when they have no income. At the end of their lives there is some inheritance, but not that much.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-4"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"PullQuote","iFrameType":"","pullQuote":"Between 1995 and 2016, only 2% of bequests equaled $1,000,000 or more &ndash; yet this money comprised upwards of 40% of wealth transferred","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-5"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003ELowell R. Ricketts, lead analyst for the Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis&rsquo;s Center for Household Financial Stability, agrees. He says that only a minority of baby boomer families will pass on &ldquo;significant wealth&rdquo;. (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.federalreserve.gov\u002Feconres\u002Fnotes\u002Ffeds-notes\u002Fhow-does-intergenerational-wealth-transmission-affect-wealth-concentration-20180601.htm\"\u003EJune 2018 figures\u003C\u002Fa\u003E from the US Federal Reserve confirm this: between 1995 and 2016, only 2% of bequests equaled $1,000,000 or more &ndash; yet this money comprised upwards of 40% of wealth transferred.)\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough some assets by nature do retain value or even appreciate, Ricketts says, we cannot assume that baby boomers will hold onto assets until bequest. &ldquo;A home and the property it&rsquo;s built on may need to be liquidated in retirement to maintain a standard of living. Therefore, even if those assets don&rsquo;t disappear from the economy, they might not be retained and passed on.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETried-and-true plan B\u003C\u002Fstrong\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEven if the transfer of assets occurred and it also significantly impacted millennial wealth, says Ricketts, timing is a crucial factor.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn the St. Louis Fed&rsquo;s \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.stlouisfed.org\u002Fhousehold-financial-stability\u002Fthe-demographics-of-wealth\u002Fwealth-impacts-of-great-recession-on-young-families\"\u003EDemographics of Wealth\u003C\u002Fa\u003E summary, researchers write that American wealth accumulation for households headed by someone born in the 1980s are 34% percent below expectations. &ldquo;These families are approaching important financial milestones (homeownership, raising children, saving for retirement) with diminished wealth accumulation,&rdquo; says Ricketts. &ldquo;A windfall in the future won&rsquo;t help these families meet their current financial obligations. In other words, the promise of a transfer in the future won&rsquo;t help meet the down payment required for a mortgage.&rdquo;\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-6"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[]},"cardType":"Image","iFrameType":"","image":["p06tns6t"],"imageAlignment":"centre","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-7"},{"bodyHtml":{"assets":[],"html":"\u003Cp\u003EIf you are among the millennials crossing your fingers for surprise cash infusion, then Donovan&rsquo;s model likely doesn&rsquo;t apply to you. Waiting on a windfall can&rsquo;t be your plan A &ndash; and, even then, you might be waiting too long.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EAs elder generations continue to struggle with retirement savings and \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.bbc.com\u002Fnews\u002Fhealth-43726436\"\u003Elive longer\u003C\u002Fa\u003E on less, millennials looking to save for retirement might want to keep courting the tried-and-true option: socking away money with lower-volatility vehicles. The silver lining of higher interest rates in the economy is not nearly as thrilling as found wealth, sure. But aren&rsquo;t millennials used to taking what they can get?\u003C\u002Fp\u003E"},"cardType":"Body","iFrameType":"","id":"worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181205-with-boomers-wealth-to-inherit-will-millennials-get-rich-8"}],"collection":["worklife\u002Fpremium-collection\u002Fgeneration-project"],"disableAdverts":false,"displayDate":"2018-12-06T15:31:35Z","embeddedCustomHtml":"","embeddedInfographicUrl":"","embeddedType":"","geolocation":null,"headlineLong":"Are millennials on track to become the richest generation?","headlineShort":"When do millennials get to be rich?","image":["p06tnsbx"],"imageAlignment":"centre","imageAltText":"","isSyndicated":true,"latitude":"","location":null,"longitude":"","mpsVideo":"","option":[{"Content":{"Description":"Apple News Publish: Select to publish, remove to unpublish. (Do not just delete or unpublish the story)","Name":"publish-applenews-system-1"},"Metadata":{"CreationDateTime":"2016-02-05T14:32:31.186819Z","Entity":"option","Guid":"13f4bc85-ae27-4a34-9397-0e6ad3619619","Id":"option\u002Fpublish-applenews-system-1","ModifiedDateTime":"2016-02-05T14:32:31.186819Z","Project":"","Slug":"publish-applenews-system-1"},"Urn":"urn:pubstack:jative:option:option\u002Fpublish-applenews-system-1","_id":"5e9821532567d5de226b3500"}],"partner":null,"primaryVertical":"worklife","promoAlignment":"centre","promoAltText":"","promoImage":["p06tnsbz"],"relatedStories":["worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181204-how-austerity-memes-helped-the-internet-generation-cope","worklife\u002Farticle\u002F20181109-who-should-be-able-to-afford-affordable-housing"],"relatedTag":null,"summaryLong":"If boomers are the wealthiest generation ever, then millennials should be poised to become rich through inheritance. The principle is correct – but the reality is more complicated.","summaryShort":"Will millennials be the wealthiest generation ever?","tag":["tag\u002Fwealth","tag\u002Fmillennials"],"creationDateTime":"2018-12-05T21:00:25.663416Z","entity":"article","guid":"642f1cae-453b-448b-9638-7f